{"word":"κοπρίας","slug":"κοπρίας","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n58991\" key=\"kopri/as\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κοπρ-ίας</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ου</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">κόπρος</etym>) in pl., <sense id=\"n58991.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">buffoons</tr_>, a word first used under the Roman emperors, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0385.tlg001:50:28\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.C.\">D.C.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">50.28</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0385.tlg001:73:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">73.6</biblScope> </bibl>: Lat. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">copreae</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:latinLit:phi1348.phi013:61\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Suet.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Tib.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">61</biblScope></bibl>. (Perh. so called because <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐκ κοπρίας ἀναιρεθέντες</foreign>, or because of their obscenity.)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}